analysis: The documents primarily concern land use and reservations in Alaska, including establishing military ranges, transferring property to the State of Alaska, creating military reservations, designating sites for federal buildings, excluding land from national forests for homesites, revoking power-site reserves, reserving land for school purposes, reserving land for telegraph systems, establishing reindeer stations, and modifying townsite reservations for road building. The documents reflect a historical period of active federal land management and resource allocation in Alaska.
title: Alaskan Land Allocation and Federal Management
